        "id": 1002462
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-24T09:04:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You are correct; the startup process is working exactly as expected during boot. Regarding the CLI behavior, the reason it doesn\u0027t generate the log is likely because the standard reboot command bypasses the D-Bus/Redfish graceful shutdown flow, thereby avoiding the state manager\u0027s transition logic entirely.",
      "parentUuid": "4ed75baf_a6034cd4",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 18,
        "startChar": 38,
        "endLine": 21,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "11988f7cb3367e3e1c01e58df197511cf45fdc6a",
