        "id": 1000004
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-06T20:03:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m still not a huge fan of this, it feels like we\u0027re working around something I wasn\u0027t super happy to begin with (the log on every state change). Going to NotReady on a reboot was added because at least at IBM, our external Redfish clients kept hitting a window during the BMC reboot where they thought the BMC was still \"Ready\" and was expecting normal Redfish API\u0027s to keep working. BMC reboots take 10-15s and bmcweb is the last to get shut down so it was a mess. Going to NotReady is an indicator to external clients to stop talking to the BMC in these reboot paths. \n\nBut with all that said, add a comment to the code and I\u0027m fine.",
      "revId": "11988f7cb3367e3e1c01e58df197511cf45fdc6a",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
